Took my son to see the Beastie Boys exhibition in LA
.
When I was exactly his age this was my favorite band no questions asked! It was a must when I found out there was an exhibit showcasing near our house! Felt good as a father to show him part of hiphop history and explain what the Beastie boys did for me & our culture. Still one of my favorites to this day (call me ol school ). I explained to him my earliest memory of me DJ’ing at his age in Boston blasting the license to ill cassette tape from my moms boombox in to the streets of the city (speakers facing out) all day long! Looking back I don’t remember any supervision either 🤣 shout out to my mom for buying the cassette tape that forever changed my life.👌 after leaving Tre mentions that he knows more beastie boys songs than he thought and continues to dive in to the discography taking a liking to  Brass monkey of corse 🫡🤣 thank you @beyondthestreetsart  for hosting such a great exhibit.💯💯 thanks @extra_medium_ for the free passes 🙌
.
